C D 669L.course_description:
Prerequisites:
1) Completion of all disorder-specific graduate seminars;
2) completion of a minimum of 3 core clinics (C D 669A -C D 669J );
3) C D 483  and C D 489 , or equivalent as approved by the instructor) and consent of instructor.Assessment/management of speech-language disorders in clients whose native language is different than that of the clinician. Training of bilingual interpreters.Letter grade only (A-F). Minimum 25 clock hours required. Course fee may be required.

