3) SLP 483  and SLP 489 , or equivalent as approved by the instructor) and consent of instructor.Assessment/management of speech-language disorders in clients whose native language is different than that of the clinician. Training of bilingual interpreters.Letter grade only (A-F). Minimum 25 clock hours required. Course fee may be required.
